  "body": "## Bug Report\r\n\r\n**What version of Rust are you using?**\r\nrustc 1.29.0-nightly (4f3c7a472 2018-07-17)\r\n\r\n**What operating system and CPU are you using?**\r\nCentos 7.3\r\n\r\n**What did you do?**\r\nWriting data continuously.\r\n\r\n**What did you expect to see?**\r\nLeader will be elected as soon as split finished.\r\n\r\n**What did you see instead?**\r\nI find that if region split happens, the new generated region can't elect a leader for about 2 seconds. After some investigation, i found that two followers applied split command 2 seconds after it has applied in leader. If i turn off `skip_bcast_commit`, this delay will go away.",
